text: this isnt even all of my struggles from the last 6 months of this life. there is so much more about all this that i wish no one will ever have to experience in their lives. this shit is not easy at ALL

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: 8. driving. i got my licenses when i turned 16. i didn’t even drive for 2 years and now i cant at all. i can not go anywhere by myself i have to have someone with me at all times to get me somewhere due to not being able to press my foot down on the pedals

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: 7. getting in a car. i have to either be picked up and sat in the car or use a slide board to get in a car now. and i cant keep my balance going around curves meaning im falling over in the car constantly

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: 6. picking up my daughter. i lost so my muscle from being in a hospital bed for a month i cant even lift my daughter anymore. someone has to hand her to me to even hold her now cause of how big shes getting. its hard for me to even change her diaper now

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: 5. showering and bathing. i can not bathe by myself anymore. i have to have help cause i cant get my arms fully above my head to even wash my hair. and if i do get them above my head i loose my balance and start to fall over

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: 4. getting dressed. people don’t understand how hard the EASIEST daily task is for me now. it used to take 5min tops for me to get dressed. it now takes 30-45mins to get dressed cause i have to fight my spasms and body to move to roll around in bed to get pants on

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: 3. spasms. my legs jerk, shake, bounce, curl up, straighten out, ect. once again just because my leg moves doesnt mean im doing it or have control over it. i have no control over spasms and they absolutely drain my body energy to get through a day with them

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: 2. using the bathroom. i cannot use the bathroom in any aspect. i rely on a bowel program (please dont look up what it is if you dont want to stare at your screen like”what-?😃”) to use the bathroom along with a catheter to do the rest. i have no bowel or bladder control at all

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: 1. walking. i can not walk anymore. i rely on a wheelchair to get me from point A to point B. just because i can lift and move my leg DOES. NOT. MEAN. I. CAN. WALK. YET.

text: you never know what could happen. this has been the scariest experience of my life. we have no idea if im even going to be able to walk again but we are trying our best. let this post be a lesson. if you feel off. go get checked dont put it off.

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: this was the last thing i ever expected to happen to me. i was healthy as could be. doing all my daily stuff while being a mom and in the snap of a finger i was almost gone. please never ignore signs and never take what you are able to do in life for granted

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
text: that could’ve possibly failed. saturday will be my 2 week mark in the hospital. i was lucky enough to make it out alive and say ive made it to rehab to regain my strength and hopefully walk again. please never ignore signs. you never know what could happened

author: ࿔*:･. 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐞
